   <body>
      <context>
         <note type="warning">
            <p>Batteries give off flammable fumes that can explode.</p>
            <p>Do not smoke when observing the battery electrolyte levels.</p>
            <p>Electrolyte is an acid and can cause personal injury if it contacts skin or eyes.</p>
            <p>Always wear protective glasses when working with batteries.</p>
         </note>
         <fig id="fig_ixb_ryz_5gc">
            <image href="media/image934.png" id="image_kxb_ryz_5gc" placement="inline"/>
         </fig>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Install drive wheel. Put two nuts opposite each other (180°).</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Inspect tightness of wheel nuts in a sequence opposite each other to 750 N·m (550
        lb·ft).</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
